103.6	The_Roots	The Roots	The Roots is an American hip hop/neo soul band formed in 1987 by Tariq "Black Thought" Trotter and Ahmir "Questlove" Thompson in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. They are known for a jazzy, eclectic approach to hip hop which includes live instrumentals. Malik B., Leonard "Hub" Hubbard, and Josh Abrams were added to the band, originally called The Square Roots.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/The_Roots_2007.jpg/220px-The_Roots_2007.jpg
